<h3>Component Semantics:</h3>
<component tag=Binding-Site>
  <definition> <conceptref name=Region> on the surface of a molecule - typically a                          cavity or groove - that is complementary in <conceptref name=shape> to                           another molecule (the ligand) and therefore can bind it                          through the formation of multiple weak (noncovalent)                          bonds. cf Alberts:ECB:G-3. </definition>
